OL,6,F"As to why they went to that house on
OL,7,Fthat night, and as to why they did
OL,8,Fwhat they did, these are not matters
OL,9,Fwhich the prosecution need to prove.
OL,10,FIt may never be possible to know why.
OL,12,F"Only the would-be killers or those
OL,13,Finvolved in the enterprise may know
OL,14,Fthat, and for obvious reasons, you may
OL,15,Fthink, they would never reveal it."
OL,17,FThe defendants were both remanded in
OL,18,Fcustody and will be sentenced by Mr
OL,19,FJustice Wall on Thursday.
